			}
, 			{
				"box" : 				{
					"id" : "obj-38",
					"maxclass" : "newobj",
					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 231.0, 95.0, 104.0, 20.0 ],
					"text" : "s RomBang"
				}

			}
, 			{
				"box" : 				{
					"id" : "obj-35",
					"linecount" : 39,
					"maxclass" : "comment",
					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 15.0, 167.0, 416.0, 442.0 ],
					"text" : "Machine template can be changed inside the MachineTemplate sub patch. The 2 overlay templates are meant to be partial templates to be use after you randomize all machines etc. The first template sets a random kick/snare on the first 2 pads and a control all, ram r1, and ram p1 on the last 3 pads. The second overlay sets both ram record/play machines to the last 4 pads. The overlay templates are changed in the Overlay1Template or Overlay2Template subpatches.\n\nRand Machine will randomize all 16 machines with different drum synths. No midi, gnd, ctrl, rom, or ram machines will used when randomized. Rand Rom will randomize all 16 pads with rom machines. The rom samples will be randomly selected from the first 16 sample slots.\n\nParam shuffle randomizes all 24 params for each of the 16 machines. The track level volume is not effected. \n\nFX shuffle has upper limits to the EQ and DYN gain param so sound doesn't get excessively loud. This is not the most helpful section to randomize.\n\nLFO Shuffle randomizes all 16 lfo's and destinations. Surprisingly, this ends up being one of the more interesting/inspiring parts of this patch. \n\nMax all volume will set all the volume levels (in routing screen) to 100, and set the EQ and DNY levels to around 75%. This button is used after you hit the param shuffle and hear little or no sound.\n\nCenter all pan will center the panning of all 16 machines. Often when you hear a cool result of randomization it happens to be panned strange.\n\nStrip SRR Turns off the sample rate reduction for all 16 channels. There is still the possibility of an lfo controlling the SRR level, but this helps a lot when you are randomizing.\n\nStrip Del/Rev will set all the reverb and delay levels to 0 for all pads. Sometimes it is easier to set them all to 0 and then add reverb or delay by hand. \n\n\nRyan Gilmore\nkill.inductive@gmail.com\nhttps://soundcloud.com/inductiveone"
				}

			}
, 			{
